Guide.title: Tips and Tricks Sections
Guide.Content: Search all over the maps for valuables. These will provide you with money. There are lots to be found and the more money you get, the more upgrades you can get for your weapons. Look in all the rooms you come across, check under places, and smash open things to find them.

Guide.title: Guide 1
Guide.Content:
Save often. Just in case you make a mistake, or destroy something you shouldnt. Oops. It helps to save before you test out a route, so if it doesnt work, you can go back and try something else without having to restart the mission.
Use the spraycan to mark your route. Further on in the game, when youre racing against the clock, its easy to forget where all the markers are. Use spray paint to draw your route so its easy to follow, when youre rushing to escape.

Guide.title: Guide 2
Guide.Content:
Go back to a level when you have more tools. As you progress, more tools will be delivered to you, and youll be able to unlock upgrades if youve been collecting those valuables. Go back to missions when youre better equipped â€“ especially if you missed optional objectives the first time around.
Use vehicles in your mission routes. Check around the map to see what kind of vehicles are available to use. You want to try and avoid wasting time by simply running, if possible, and have cars to take you from one objective to another. Test to see which ones are the fastest or most reliable.

Guide.title: Guide 3
Guide.Content:
Line cars up so you can jump straight into them. Following on from the above point, if youre using a car in a route, position it so you can leap straight onto it and drive off in seconds once youve completed an objective.
Do the same (as above) for boats. The same rules that apply to vehicles also apply to boats on these maps. Try them out and line them up so you can zip around maps with ease.

Guide.title: Guide 4
Guide.Content: Safes and boxes that are wired can sometimes be moved. As long as you dont break the wire, some of these can be moved closer to where you need them to be. This can shave down seconds when youre racing against the clock.

Guide.title: Guide 5
Guide.Content:
Clear the debris! When youre blowing things up, youll get debris everywhere. This can sometimes slow you down, particularly if youre planning to drive through those brand new holes in the walls. Clearing your debris creates a clearer path and ultimately, a quicker mission completion time.
Or use the debris... as blocks to jump on, as bridges, ramps or to fill gaps. Be creative with it!
Planks are really useful! Use them for ramps, to fill gaps, attach objects to cars, or to stop things from falling out when youre speeding away.

Guide.title: Guide 6
Guide.Content:
Plan your route backwards. Sometimes, its best to work out the way to go by using your end goal as the marker. This will help you think more creatively about the paths you need to take.

Its safe to say that there are a few missions in the Teardown campaign that are a challenge! While most of the walkthrough takes you through how to complete both the required and optional objectives for each mission, some need a little more preparation and practice to fully complete the objectives.

Guide.title: Guide 7
Guide.Content: In this section, youll find detailed walkthroughs on how to setup those challenging missions and the steps youll need to take to complete them.
